 Job Description
 The primary function of the Valet Living Support Representative (Customer Service Representative) is to serve as a liaison between clients/residents and Valet Living. The Customer Service Representative (CSR) will manage large amounts of inbound and outbound calls, emails, live chats, web leads and more, and document all communications, resolve client and resident complaints and initiate client satisfaction phone calls and digital surveys. The CSR must have a strong technology background and be willing to bring new ideas to the Valet Living Support team.
 Job Responsibilities
 Identify client and resident (customer) needs, clarify information, research every issue and provide standard-setting solutions and/or alternatives
 Answer or make calls to clients to learn about and address their needs, complaints or other issues
 Answer live chats immediately and be able to respond to situations quickly
 Engage in active listening with callers, confirming or clarifying information and delighting angry clients and residents
 Enthusiastically recommend products or services to clients and potential clients at every reasonable opportunity
 Build sustainable relationships and engage clients and residents by going the extra mile
 Keep records of all conversations in our Salesforce database in a comprehensible way
 Become subject matter expert on all brand verticals in order to provide knowledgeable answers to questions about product, pricing and availability
 Work with internal departments to meet clientsâ€™ needs
 Escalate issues as needed to various management teams
 Utilize software, databases, scripts and tracking tools appropriately
 Serve as an outstanding brand ambassador
 Perform other duties to include (but not limited to) answering reception phones, replying to email requests, etc.
 Education and Experience Requirements
 High School diploma required
 A minimum of 2 yearsâ€™ prior customer care experience
 Bilingual (English/Spanish) required
 Outbound call center/inside sales experience is a plus
 Technology background
 Hospitality/concierge background is a plus
 Knowledge, Skills and Abilities
 Outstanding customer service skills to include empathy, verbal communication, and follow-up with a sense of urgency
 High energy, results-driven attitude
 Familiarity with innovative call center practices such as live chat, web, text and Artificial Intelligence (AI)
 Technical savvy and ability to learn about our software and hardware
 Excellent skills in data analysis, communication and problem solving
 Familiarity with CRM systems and practices
 Adaptability to different personality types
 Outstanding communication skills: written, verbal and listening
 Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications including Excel, Word and PowerPoint
 Prospecting skills â€“ comfortable with repetitive work and cold calling
 Ability to demonstrate a professional demeanor at all time
 Ability to speak clearly and project friendly voice tone
 Ability to accurately document and present information during phone interactions
 Comfort with multi-tasking and working in a fast pace environment while managing time effectively
